            <p>a and b. <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> by his parents <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></p><p>c. <note>not translatable though possiby from <foreign xml:lang="la">concordia</foreign>, concord.</note></p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The three fragments have been re-examined since 1951. The two fragments a and b should be taken together: the stones do not make an exact juncture, but the graining of the marble shows that they did in fact adjoin.</p>
